Aug 7 2009	You get what you pay for	Booked this hotel for its less than $30 a night price, and received what should be expected at that price. The hotel staff weren't friendly but did what they were there to do. It was a long walk through the smokey casino (of course, that's how they do it in Vegas) to get to the South Tower elevators (although thankfully, there are 3 sets of doors that lead outside at various spots throughout the casino so you can brave the heat if you'd rather not walk through the casino). The room was old, the furniture chipped and worn, the wallpaper peeling, and the floor dirty (when we first walked in you could see the vacuum marks, only the main paths through the room had been vacuumed). The bathroom was fairly clean. We had a good view of the pool and the Fremont Street Experience from our room. The bed and pillows were pretty comfortable and no one woke up sore.It is however in a great spot, at the end of the Fremont St Experience. To get the most food for your money at this hotel, eat at the grill next to the South Tower Elevators. I got a cheeseburger and steak fries for about $6 and it definitely filled me up. However, the Paradise Buffet at the Fremont (just down the street) offered breakfast, lunch, and dinner buffets from around $6-8 per person with a good selection of food.If you want to go down to the strip, ride The Deuce public bus system. The buses are clean although sometimes crowded and they drop-off right at downtown on Fremont. If you're going to ride it more than 5 times/be there at least 3 days, I HIGHLY recommend getting the $15 3-day bus pass (it's also good for any other Vegas public bus). If you're going out of town (ie. Hoover Dam or Red Rock Canyon, which I highly recommend, at $5 per car it's a great Vegas deal) it's easiest to just rent a car. DO NOT TAKE A TAXI, they are -very expensive- (our taxi ride from the airport to downtown to the Plaza cost us $36).Overall I won't complain much about the hotel because of the price. If you just want somewhere to sleep and shower in Vegas and don't care about having an updated/spotless room then this hotel is for you, you certainly can't beat the price.	
