Jun 21 2008 	Great for the money - more improvements coming	If you want glitz and glamour, go pay $$$$ and stay on the strip. Yes, this place is old. But for the money you pay, it is perfect if you want a getaway to party and gamble. Some rooms are better than others, but they are all large (except for the bathrooms). Some recent improvements include the new lounge they opened on the casino floor which has live entertainment most nights for free. They were also getting ready to open the new check in desk now on the first floor directly in front of the main doors. I'm sure that will make many people happy. They were having elevator problems while I was there, and a couple of the north elevators were out of service while they waited for parts. A minor inconvenience that should be fixed by now. In all the times I've stayed here I've never had a problem getting drinks whenever I wanted one, and they tend to make them stronger than most places. Just be sure to give the waitress a tip ($1) and she'll be back often. Like I said, just don't expect the glitz of the strip, but you won't pay the price either. This is old Las Vegas and the Plaze gives you that feeling.	
