May 27 2008 	About what I expected	The hotel is nothing fancy, it is an older hotel next to the old downtown Vegas (Fremont Street) NOT near the Strip. I stayed one night on Memorial Day weekend because I wanted somewhere cheap to crash that wasn't too far from stuff to do. (I spent more on the gas from southern CA and back than I did on the room!) Having read some good and some bad reviews before booking, I spent $10 extra to get a &quot;high floor strip view&quot; deluxe room. The room was large, it was 1550 in the south tower, and it did have a good view of the strip if you're interested in that. Non-smoking room didn't particularly smell (I've had worse ones in Vegas), no plumbing problems like other people had, hot water was fine, shower head height was fine. The bathroom was small, but at least the sink was separate from the toilet/shower. The space to hang clothes was smallish and was part of the bathroom rather than a separate closet with a door, but there was an ironing board and iron. No hairdryer or coffee maker, plastic cups, only 2 soaps and a small shampoo/conditioner combo, no lotion or shoe shine or anything. The beds were older and low to the ground, but I slept ok. The air conditioner was very loud cycling on and off, but otherwise the room was quiet. Others had mentioned reception is on the third floor but this is no longer true. However, it is on the opposite side of the hotel from the parking (valet and self park are both next to the bus stop). I would drop bags in the circle by Fremont St and park later. The south tower is by the parking, the North tower is by Fremont St. and the reception area and most of the food. The front desk wasn't labeled and there was no queue as such, but even on a holiday weekend it wasn't too busy. There was the buffet and fast food but I didn't eat at any of the places there. Yes the area around the hotel was slightly sketchy but it's Vegas! There will be sex shops around especially in downtown! Honestly if you aren't comfortable with sex shops and nudity don't go to Vegas at all or leave the kids at home. Overall it was good for a cheap place for party people to crash for a few hours, bad for a weeklong romantic trip/spa trip/place to relax in the room for a while. You get what you pay for, and I was satisfied.	
