Mar 31 2008	Great Location	Just got back from 3 nights at The Plaza and despite some of what you read here &amp; other places, it was a great time. Our group had 4 room (3 adjoining) in the North Tower. Rooms were clean and reasonably well-appointed, although worn. Room size was decent &amp; staff were accomodating. Note: BRING A HAIRDRYER. This is Vegas, 60's style. No extras or frills. No in-room coffee maker. But if you're looking for a fun, affordable spot downtown, this is it. Never felt ill at ease or uncomfortable with entering or leaving the property, even late at night. Hotel security &amp; Fremont Street security do a nice job. The buffet was decent &amp; a Subway &amp; McDonald's onsite came in handy. The coffee shop staff was a bit pokey &amp; lines got long in the a.m., but all in all, I was very pleased &amp; would return to the Plaza. Have fun!	
