Mar 28 2008 	Decent price decent rooms	Went with a group of friends and decided to book some inexpensive rooms to save money for other activities (like losing it at the blackjack tables). Booked four rooms all next to each other at the Plaza at a very reasonable $80 a piece for the double queen option. Was pleasantly surprised by the overall size of the rooms, one was big enough to fit everyone in our party (9 total) comfortably to watch an early morning college football game. Combined with the opened attaching doors between rooms, it made for a vary spacious environment for everyone to relax in. The bathrooms were rather small though and they had a strangely architectured entryway which is narrower than a regular door's width. Location was pretty good, being at the end of Fremont Street...didn't try out the pool, tennis courts or gym so can't comment on those. Casino was a little on the small side with not a large variety of table games, but ajoining casinos offered some respite to my gambling vices. Didn't try any internal restaurants, but I do recommend making the trip to the Planet Hollywood Casino's buffett...very, very good in my opinion and not too expensive at $28 per person. A fun weekend trip with the guys and would stay here again if another deal came up.	
