Dec 18 2007 	Ok for the money!!	We stayed at the Plaza on a Friday night in October. This was a planned trip and the next three nights we stayed up on the strip. The Plaza location is great right at the end of Freemont Street. Our room overlooked the street, but you really couldn't see a whole lot because of the roof. Check in was fast, but the clerk was very short with us, and didn't have much of a sense of humor. The room was very clean, but also very outdated. The bathroom was very small and old. The Casino was a real suprise. I really liked the casino, of course it always helps when you win. We ate at the $7.77 buffet. The food was ok, especially for the price. The only real bad thing I can say about the Plaza was the elevators. We were on one of the top floors and with only one bank of elevators that stopped at almost every floor, the wait was a long one. Overall I would say the Plaza is good, considering what you pay for. If you are used to staying in the fancy hotels on the strip, you may want to avoid this one.	
