Nov 4 2007 	It's a room	You need to be realistic about staying at this hotel. You're getting a room for under $100 in Las Vegas. On the plus side: parking is free, the hotel has easy freeway access and is literally across the street from the Fremont Light Experience, which is fun to see. It's also centrally located in downtown to walk around and explore other casinos. On the negative side - the entire hotel is a bit shabby. In my room, every piece of furniture was nicked and scratched, the bathroom mirror was cracked and the carpets were stained. But the bathroom was clean, the bed was reasonably comfortable and I didn't go to Vegas to sit in my room. Experiences with the staff at check-in and at the buffet were fine. I'm giving this place an average rating because it met my expectations for a room that costs less than $100 per night in Las Vegas.	
