Aug 6 2007 	cheesy but fun	I have stayed in the Plaza, Las Vegas quite a few times because it's cheap and close to the 'Freemont Street Experience'. The hotel is fairly grubby - doesn't look like it's been updated for 20+ yrs. However, I love the rooms - they're huge! They have two double beds, 2 cosy chairs and a bathroom and small dressing area. However, this is in the South Tower - the North Tower rooms are smaller and pretty depressing. The casino is wonderfully cheesy - though I never won a penny on the video poker machines. The hotel used to have a great diner - it's still there but no longer serves fab food.Shame. I wouldn't touch the buffet there - looks horrendous and the food outlet in the casino is lousy. Overall,the hotel is cheap and basic but if you just want a bed for the night it's fine.	
