Jul 13 2007 	Yeah you get what you pay for.	My husband and I decided to stay at the Plaza during one part of our honeymoon. We chose the plaza because of it's location and price. We wanted to be near Freemont St and didn't want to pay more than $50 a night. We got both with the Plaza. However, we also got a view of the freeway and construction, not one of Freemont street which we had requested. When we asked about it, the front desk told us they didn't have any rooms on that side for us. The room itself wasn't terribly bad, it wasn't worse or better than we expected. It seemed kind of old, and wasn't as clean as it could have been, but since we're not terribly picky, we didn't mind, especially since we weren't planning on spending a TON of time in the room. We were originally planning on staying for 3 nights, but after the first night we decided to continue on a couple days early and spend the next two nights in Mesquite, which we did and were quite happy with. The front desk didn't give us any problems when we checked out early, and we appreciated that. All in all it was an alright stay but we are staying in another hotel for our Vegas trip this year.	
