Jul 3 2007 	Perfect for those on a budget! Experience old-school Vegas...	If you are on a budget and want to experience Vegas as it may have existed 30+ years ago, the Plaza is a great choice. We stayed at the Plaza for 3 nights in Aug. 2006, and we were pleasantly surprised. The check-in staff was helpful and friendly. We requested a non-smoking room with 2 double beds, and we got that. During check-in I also requested a high-floor room with a great view of Fremont Street, and we got that too...no &quot;$20 trick&quot; required! The room was a bit basic, kind of like what you would find at a Motel 6, but it was great for the price (see pictures of our room above). The bathroom was small, but good enough for our needs. Our room was very clean, the air conditioner worked perfectly, and the beds were comfortable. The maid service was excellent - our room was very clean everyday.The casino is large but the decor is average, nothing fancy. The hotel lobby and casino were clean. I did not notice any bad smells in the hotel. We didn't eat at any of the hotel restaurants, so I can't comment on those.We did not have any bedbugs.To sum up, at the Plaza you not only get a great vintage hotel from 70s-era Vegas, you also get the &quot;old Vegas&quot; experience of downtown, which is what we were looking for on our trip last year. Based on the value you get here, I'd give it 5 stars, and if we ever stay downtown again we will stay at the Plaza.	
