May 14 2007	Nothing wrong with the Plaza	We have played at the Plaza many times, as we love staying downtown, but this was our first time to stay at the Plaza. Needless to say, after reading the reviews on this website, we were skeptical, but decided to brave it anyway because we had free rooms from our players' cards. We don't at all regret it.Now if you're looking for luxury, do yourself a favor and get a room at the Golden Nugget. But if you're in Vegas to gamble and need a good, clean room with a nice shower and comfortable bed to sleep in, nothing wrong with the Plaza. I tipped the guy $10 when I checked in, as another person recommended and got in the North tower, which is the newer of the two. The 3rd floor check in was not that big of a deal. The elevator was right near the entrance of the hotel from the street, so very conveniently located. The rooms were old and dated but fine for a good night sleep. No cable tv, but again, we don't go for that. The bed was comfy, cold a/c, and good water pressure in the shower. The room was clean and the staff was friendly. We would stay here again.	
