Mar 18 2007 	First Time to Downtown Las Vegas	This was the first time I'd been to Downtown Las Vegas.The Plaza is in a good location for getting to the other hotels in Downtown and it's just a short walk to the bus stop for the Duece to the Strip, but if you're getting a taxi, taking the Freeway route is MUCH quicker than going down Las Vegas Blvd.The food at the Plaza is ok, the buffet seemed to be the same selection every day though, so on a couple of occasions I went to other hotels for food. The Diner is good for a late night feed, especially if your body is still in another time zone.The room I had was on the 20th floor and was very comfortable. Could do with some updating cosmetically, but it was fine as a place to rest my head. It had a great view of Downtown and some of the Strip.Overall I'd prefer to stay on the Strip next time as there's much more going on and travelling to the Strip can take an hour by bus, but my stay was nowhere near as bad as some horror stories I've read.	
Mar 13 2007 	The Plaza is getting better	My friends and I were traveling to see vegas and hang out for a few days. The week we chose to stay, I guess all the other hotels were pretty sold out (due to the races, I had no idea). To stay within budget it was between the Plaza, some other downtown hotels, and the Sahara. We ended up at the Plaza because they had a good deal for 3 nights. I was a little apprehensive because of all the mixed reviews i had read, some being really bad and some good. Well, when we arrived late at night, the outside looked much better than the pictures i had seen. They had it all done up with blue floodlights on the sides which looked really cool with the classic old blinking lights. We parked in the garage and it looked old and not well maintained, as well did the parking garage elevator lobby that we passed through. I was pleasantly suprised when i saw the checkin area was retro yet well maintained and clean. I had hopes that the bad reviews were wrong. Checkin was pretty quick, but the late night checkin clerks didnt seem very friendly. We got our keys and proceeded to our room in the south tower on the 23rd floor. When the elevator doors opened, I felt my worst fears were revealed. the hallways were horribly outdated, with stains on the carpet, etc. We got to our room and we couldnt open the door. all 3 keys didnt work. we had to go back twice and try nine keys all together with no luck. finally we got kinda short with the clerk and he gave us another room on the 22nd floor in the south tower. When the elevator doors opened this time, I was shocked! and pleasantly suprised. The halls were tastefully decorated in a garden theme with new floral carpets and picures and fake plants. I couldnt believe it...i thought we had teleported to a different hotel. we opened our room and the same theme carried on into there with all new funiture and fixtures! I was soo happy. The pool was getting remodeled so it was closed, and the bathrooms are kinda small but it was ok. We looked on the other floors in the tower and we couldnt find one in the south one that looked like ours. they were all old and not remodeled. I think some of the rooms in the north tower are though, we saw at least one. The people in the casino and buffet were very friendly, and the food was good. It was neat to walk around freemont street and gamble, much less busy than the strip. It was very pleasant, but if you stay in the near future, make sure to ask for the 22nd floor in the south tower or one in the north tower to get one of these nice rooms.	
Mar 13 2007 	Better Than Expected	We stayed at the Plaza March 4-9th. I was worried about this property based on the reviews I had read. We were in room 1848 and had a beautiful view of the strip. The rooms were larger than other hotels downtown, although the bathroom area was small. The room was old and not in the best of shape, but it was clean. We didn't have any plumbing problems as some people have stated, and the ice machine on our floor was working just fine. We were close to the elevators and ice machine, but didn't hear any noise from them. I thought the beds were going to be very uncomfortable, but I actually slept quite well. Housekeeping never bothered us early in the morning, we were always out of the room before they came. I did have some luck gambling there, but did better at the Fremont, Fitzgeralds and Main Street Station. We ate breakfast at their 24 hour cafe, and the food was fine. I prefer being more in the middle of Fremont Street, but would stay there again. I didn't find the casino to be as smokey as some have stated. Maybe it is worse on the weekend. At times it seemed quite warm in the casino compared to others, during the day it would have been too warm for me to be in for any length of time, but late at night it was actually welcomed, as we were chilly at some of the others and were not dressed very warm. All in all, I had a better experience than I was expecting to at the Plaza.	
Mar 4 2007	Good Value and Location	I stayed at the Plaza Feb 23 - 27th. Couldn't beat the price over the weekend in Vegas. Checkin went well on a Friday night and the staff were friendly and curteous. Had a high room (20th floor) with a refrigerator. The room was OK, sheets were clean, shower/plumbing worked flawlessly, ice machine worked, and their workout room had pretty good equipment (at no additional charge to use). The room itself was kind of dirty, dirt buildup in all corners and the carpet hadn't been cleaned in quite some time. I had housekeepingcome up and vacuum. I actually had to lower the vacuum down from the highest setting and it made a pretty big difference on the carpet. The housekeeping staff was very accomodating and responded quickly to my requests.I enjoyed the hotel casino. I could always get into any game and the table limits didn't price me out of anything. They have good payouts on the Video Poker as well. Of course there is lots of smoke, but somehow I felt like the smoke was worse at some of the other casinos downtown. That may have been because the Plaza just didn't have as many people.I didn't eat at the Plaza, but instead walked down to Main Street Station, Binions, and across the street at the Golden Gate diner. All these places offer great value and good eats, with Main Street Station having a fun attitude as well.Being downtown and close to Fremont street and MSS, I thought the Plaza worked out well as my home base. I have been to Vegas many times and so the strip was not somewhere I cared to visit again. I have stayed on the strip, off strip, and downtown. Downtown worked out well and I plan to stay down there again next time.As for where to stay downtown, if one can get a good rate at the Golden Nugget, it has been rejuvenated beyond expectations and is a beautiful property now. Just watch the limits and slots as they have to pay for all that glitz somehow. Their slots, for me, were the tightest of tight. As for the Plaza, it is definitely in need of some work if they want to return it to its glory days, but it works as a cheap weekend alternative to allow me gambling money instead of sleeping money. If you have both (or a wife you are treating), I would not recommend this place as a treat. If it is your fifth time out or more and you want to game and eat reasonably, it makes for a great place to stay.	
