Sep 13 2006 	Possibly the worst hotel I've stayed in	First off, let me say that I am not a picky hotel stayer. In fact, I usually stay at B&amp;Bs, so things like small rooms, or basic furnishings don't upset me. I stayed in the Plaza in July because we were attending a convention within the hotel, so it seemed convenient, and it certainly was cheap, so one might say, you get what you pay for. We thought that too, which is why we didn't complain or ask to be moved, even though our TV was not working- it had a picture but the images were so blurred, it looked like we were watching Mask. We also didn't complain about the constantly streaming faucet- not just dripping, but streaming. The things that crossed the line for me, and drove me to write this review(though I admit I waited til I was back on tripadvisor to do it- a couple months after the fact) were 2 things. First, getting my PRESCRIPTION glasses stolen from poolside and the way it was dismissed, and having maintenence enter our room the morning we were checking out despite the do not disturb sign. So, first the glasses. I guess I learned the hard way that I shouldn't have left them carefully atop the towel on my chair, because they were within view and easy to pick off, and they did have clip-ons on them so they may have just looked like sunglasses to the thief. But, man, that was heartbreaking. I can't see that well without my glasses, and didn't have any backup. I ended up wearing my boyfriend's backup pair to cirque du soleil that night. The thing that was upsetting was that we know that cameras are everywhere in casinos. We have friends who have gotten rooms comped by asking them to check the cameras and verify that they lost enough money in a casino to get their room comped, but the reply from security to my glasses (and another woman who lost sunglasses at the same time) was a shrug of the shoulders, and a &quot;We don't even check the cameras for drug deals.&quot; Maybe they just meant in the pool area, but either way, not quite what you want to hear from your hotel. The other upsetting incident was the morning we were checking out. We hung out the do not disturb sign and went to Starbucks to grab a quick breakfast before coming back to shower, collect our bags and check out. Don't ask me why my boyfriend hadn't showered before breakfast, it would've helped things, but it didn't seem to matter at the time. So, all set to do that, we walk back to our room and find the door ajar. We enter to find a maintenence man in the bathroom with the toilet IN the bathtub!! He thought we had called to have him fix the toilet which apparently wasn't securely affixed to the floor anymore, but it was the one thing that at least seemed to be working fine in the room, ironically! We were confused and said we hadn't called, and why had he come in, when the do not disturb sign was out? Who knows, no answer there. I was really angry and frustrated, because instead of just getting out of there, we had to wait another 1/2 hour for the guy to finish fixing the toilet so that my boyfriend could take his shower. Why this repair couldn't have waited to be done until after we had checked out, I can't fathom. I learned a valuable lesson there at the pool, which is pretty sad- a person can't even wear their glasses to the pool anymore for fear of having them stolen. I also learned that I will NEVER stay in the Plaza again.	
