Nov 19 2005	Great Plaza Experience	I just returned from my first stay at the Plaza in Downtown Las Vegas. Got a two bedroom suite on 23rd floor of the South Tower. Elevators are fast, however the parking garage elevators are extremely slow. The suite was two old separate renovated rooms made into a two bedroom suite. The cable t.v. selection was not too good. (One station had no sound.) Furniture was nice with two poofy couches. Bathrooms were small but you got two of them. Great views of all of the strip. Train noise was no problem. There were no wierd smells like some reviewers have indicated. Staff was very polite and helpful. Price was right and the value was definitely there. Outside the room the place needs some TLC. A lot of chipped wood that needs paint. The close-up magic show for $8.00 was a huge bargin and an awesome show. Don't miss it. I would indeed stay there again.	
Nov 8 2005	Good value	The Plaza needs an overhaul. The room we had was clean, but old. Very poor water pressure. Funny smell in the hallways and casino.On the positive side, the room rate was fantastic and the casino host was very accomodating at the end of our stay. All of the staff were friendly and pleasant at all times. The poker room was great and it is the only place that offers &quot;Sit and Go&quot; Texas Hold Em tournaments. The staff in the poker room was exceptional and because of them I kept going back. I would go back to play in the poker room, but I do not think I would stay in the hotel until it is cleaned up a bit. It was fine for me and my friend, but I would not like to stay there with my husband.	
Oct 30 2005	Loved it - dont believe everything you read!	The PLAZA Hotel (Barrick Gaming Group) Main Street, Las Vegas.I will admit I was worried, I'd read the reviews on this site for the PLAZA hotel and it seemed the standard of the hotel was much to be desired. I frankly do NOT agree. I found the hotel standard very acceptable. We've stayed in places like the Luxor and Mirage, Stratosphere and Mandalay Bay so I do have something to compare it with. The rate for the PLAZA are very cheap compared to somewhere like Mirage or Mandalay Bay, but the sheets are all at the same clean standard! We checked in about 8.30pm, no queue and the staff was very friendly and helpful. We are non smokers and asked for non smoking room, which we were given. We took our cases to the room and were very pleased with the view, we could see the Stratosphere and the view over Freemont Street had an air of excitement, we could see the street performance and people bustling about couldnt wait to get into the thick of it. Our room was very clean and extremely comfortable. (None of the odd smells that other reviews had written about) Two queen beds, phone, internet connect, sitting area, walk in wardrobe. Fantastic shower, the power was brillient (I wish mine at home was as good). We showered at different times of the day during our stay and never found the water to be anything other than hot. The only thing I could diss at all was the Air Con was a bit noisey, but after a few minutes we didnt notice it. The TV and channels were as good as any on offer on the main strip, we were a bit tired, but managed to get into the midnight poker tournement, Poker playing is our main reason for visiting Vegas, we love it. In the morning we were able to see the mountains and the rooftop swimming pool of the hotel. The buffet at the PLAZA is also very good. It is about $5.95 dollars for breakfast (Until 11am) and is very filling, with loads of choices. The waiting on staff are very pleasant and helpful, seating you very quickly indeed.The gaming at the hotel is also very good. The casino staff are all very friendly and will help with the card games explaining the rules and showing you how the 'house would do it' so you have as much chance as anybody of winning. The Poker room staff are very friendly as well and make you feel very good when you win a tournament.Yes the hotel is now one of the older hotels, but the quality provided is what you would want for a very enjoyable stay in Las Vegas. We are going again April and october 2006 and have already booked our rooms. The hotel also offer very good comps for playing in the poker room or on the tables.	
Oct 12 2005	Treated like someone special I love the Plaza.	This October was my second stay at this special hotel. I have found that just by being myself with the front desk got me that wonderful feeling of welcome that no amount of money can buy. The women behind the front desk worked hard to get me everything I even slightly mentioned...(i.e., iron, ironing board, direct view of Fremont, and beyond that even managed to get me a comp room for a non-smoker which made that guest ecstatic). Every (and I'm not exaggerating) employee we had contact with seemed truly to be happy. This reflects highly on managment of this property. The Plaza has the American Bandstand slot machine, which weighed heavily on my decision to originally stay there. This trip the one I chose to play was uncomfortably loud, but just a mention to a floor worker and that was corrected within 10 minutes...excellent response time in anyone's book&quot;. The food is great and is so affordable. I splurged with a $300 hit on the ABS machine and ate at The Center Stage restaurant with a direct line view of the The Experience, salmon was superb, piano musician devine, waiter was awesome ans genuinely funny and entertaining. I can recommend the Plaza entertainment especially the lounge. I love to be entertained while playing my slots. Reportcard on this special place...A++.	
