Jun 23 2005	Downtown is sweet!	I had my doubts about the Plaza after reading some of the reviews here, but taking my college age son and roommate for their first trip needed to be cheap, and downtown Vegas is a bargain. We had the south tower room with a view of the mountains and the strip, it was great. Rooms were decent and had no problems with plumbing, although I suppose the maid service was a little slow. The bathroom area is pretty tight but not that unexpected in older hotels. Nothing fancy, just average, but I did love Fremont Street at night. Its like a big block party and very cozy. It doesn't have all the fancy mega casinos facades and fountains and roller coaster that the strip has, but so much easier to wander around and you can find cheaper gambling and better odds. The Plaza had lounge acts every night in the casino and a decent poker set-up. This is not a fancy super casino, its old school Vegas, but I like the feel.	
