Jun 22 2005	Really great deal for the price	If you are going to Vegas to party, gamble, and have fun and don't mind downtown this is the place. Very friendly staff though a non-smoking room is near impossible to get. We did have a room that overlooked Fremont street with a window that opened pleasantly (though the Zamphir wind pipes drove my husband insane). Great views, huge rooms. The rooftop pool is cool in retro kind of way. Eat at the Golden gate across the street (bay City diner or the deli) or Main Street Station (triple 7) for better food/value though the &quot;dome&quot; is cool and fancy (Deniro and Stone ate there in Casino). I'm not sure what people who didn't like this hotel expected for the price. Downtown is seedier and older and more smokey than the strip, but more real gamblers and less gawkers. Though I prefer staying at the strip (Imperial Palace-Flamingo area), this is a fun alternative that is very very reasonable.	
