Nov 10 2004 	Don't Stay Downtown	I was in town for a conference held at the Golden Nugget. That hotel was booked, so I stayed at the Plaza. It was horrible. The staff was rude, the casino was full of smoke, and the clientele was scary. The only positive aspect of this hotel was the price. It was cheap...and for a reason. If you're going to Vegas and you're on a tight budget, my advice is to stay at one of the cheaper hotels on the north end of the strip. The Sahara, the Stardust, and/or Riveria are just as affordable and more convenient to the strip. I'm glad I saw the Fremont Experience; the next time I visit Las Vegas, I can skip the downtown area completely and so should you!	
