Oct 22 2004	So-so	The Plaza Hotel has seen better days. It definitely needs refurbishing. We stayed there in April 2004 and July 2004 (4th the of July weekend).The place is more run-down than anything. Folks have gotten to calling it a &quot;Vintage Vegas&quot; hotel. Our rooms were generally clean, but everything - carpets, wallpaper, etc. - is worn out. Bedding was clean, but knowing the place was old made you wonder how they kept things up.The Plaza came under new ownership this year and you would think/hope they'd have some ideas for improvements. The casino is smaller and older, lots of those new electronic slots with the traditional ones mixed in.Lots of reservations places list it as a 3 or 4 star because of the pool, 2 tennis courts, number of restaurants, etc, but it's really just a really big and old Best Western in my opinion. When I think of a 4-star I think Sunset Station, MGM, etc. - you can put a pool and tennis courts in my yard and does not make my home a 4-star hotel.We stay there because room rates are low, $20 a night on hotelkingdom in April, and then after our first stay we were offered any 7 nights (including holidays) in 6 months for free. It's a place to drop off our bags. We don't usually eat there - they have a Chinese buffet (didn't look as good as a Panda Express), Diner-style coffee-shop, scary snack bar, Seattle's best coffee, and a McDonalds - but for less money you can find better food a block away.Room rates range from $20 to $80+ (holiday weekends) but the Golden Nugget down the street has regular $49 deals and you can even find rooms for that price on the strip.If you stay here because it's cheap, but find yourself going eleswhere for food, entertainment, gambling, etc. then you should just stay somewhere else to begin with. We never used all of our free nights - that should tell you something.	
