Apr 21 2004	Unbeatable Fun	My 1st visit to Vegas in March 2004. I stayed in the Plaza with a room facing the Fremont Street light shows, which are amazing. The room was big, clean and comfertable. The hotel staff were very friendly, and the breakfasts were excellent. The gambling is the cheapest I found in Downtown, and the atmosphere here was the best I encountered from both Downtown and on The Strip. This is definately &quot;real&quot; Vegas compared to the commercialism on The Strip. Overall a fantastic 5 days and I can't wait to go back. I highly recommend this hotel.	
