Mar 16 2004	cheap but smells	It's sad to see that what once was a really classy place is now just a dinosaour compared to the new corperate giants. The Rooms are relatively small but good value for the price about 20 dollars weekday, 45 weekend. The bathrooms are so small it feels like your going into a closet. They are rather clean however. The casino is average. One thing that stands out is this incredible smell in the air, i do not know if it is from cigars or the air conditioning , but , it really stinks inside. I think the big pluses of staying here is - 1) the price and location - you cannot beat it. 2) the place seems very secure. 3) if you just need a place to crash after an all night gambling spree this is a good place. 4) Its nice than a motel. Do not come here for - 1) a honeymoon 2) to impress someone 3) for a luxurious pamering experience. Over all this is a place i would consider coming to again , if I come with a bunch of friends and all I want is a place to crash. If youre on a budget go fo it.	
Mar 13 2004	If you enjoy stained carpets and winos.	If you are in need of a room, bad, and you can't find a place to stay - you can probably get a room at this joint. If seeing drunks and derelicts sleeping in the sports book area would trouble you, don't stay here. In fact, if being around derelicts bothers you, don't stay here.I have seen things at this hotel that I've not seen in ghettos. I was playing black jack. An elderly lady walks by the tables and she is holding a tissue against her face. She moved her hand and the tissue fell - she picked it up and stuck it back against her face. No, she was not crying, she was not injured - she was some sort of bag lady probably looking for a toilet and a corner to sleep in. Did the pit boss summon security to boot her out? Of course not, this is the rule at Plaza. They have penny slots - what more need I say?This hotel is also the location of the Greyhound bus depot. It figures.The rooms are decent size but the carpets are filthy. They have a parking ramp so that's a plus. The rest of the joint is should be rated a minus 4 stars. Stay here if you are broke or can't find somewhere else to stay. It's a last resort.	
