Feb 2 2004	Very Pleasant Stay	A friend and I stayed at the Plaza in June of 2003 and we thought it was very nice. The room we shared was very large and pleasant not like some of the newer hotels where you can barely turn around without bumping into each other. We loved being across the street from the Fremont District's light show and away from the busy, noisy strip. We had read some bad reviews of the hotel and didn't know what to expect, but we enjoyed our stay very much. The place was well kept up. The free-with-one drink impersonator show was awesome! The young man did great impersonations. The price was great and we'd stay again.	
