Sep 17 2003	Friends Married Here	Stayed at the Plaza 29th August - 7th September 2003. The friend I travelled with has stayed at the Plaza before and thoroughly enjoyed it so suggested her son use it as a venue for his wedding. The staff were very efficient in the main. The cashiers were very friendly, always had a smile and time for a chat. A few miseries on reception on occasion! We were kept &quot;well watered&quot; in the casino. The wedding was first class, although brief. Ok, so it is a little shabby in places and we did have a leaky ice machine on our floor (24th), but I suppose the price reflects this. We had an excellent view of the Strip from our room (2430) in the South Tower. There is an excellent bus service the other end of Freemont Street. The #301 bus travels the length of the Strip. For $5 you can buy a 24 hour ticket and get on and off as much as you like. Good value when a single journey is $2.I would definitely stay here again. The Strip is a little too busy and &quot;in your face&quot; for me.	
