Aug 23 2003	Not Great Not Horrific	I stayed at the Plaza twice. August 5-8, 2003 and August 10-13, 2003. I found a cheaper place to stay on the weekend when the prices at the Plaza flew sky high. Overall, it's not a bad place. The first stay, I was in the South Tower, 8th Floor. It was clean enough, bathroom's tiny, and yes, it is worn. Unfortunately, on my last day, while checking to see if I left anything behind, I looked under the beds and there were a previous man's crumpled up socks underneath the bed! Meaning it's been there for days and may still be there! Pretty gross, I must say. The second stay was worse, I was in the South Tower, once again, in 1035 and the room just smells of urine. As soon as I walked in there, I could smell it. It helped to turn up the AC, unfortunately, the maids would constantly turn it off if I was out of the room, which was all the time, so I'd come back to a smelly room everyday. The 8th floor maids put the AC on full blast so I'm not sure what the deal is there. The bed had a wooden frame/support so there was no way any strangers' socks would be found. Perhaps that explains why the maids didn't check under the beds on the first stay. Upon check out, I asked the woman (British accent?) a simple question : 'How do I get to the airport?' She hadn't a clue, and told me to go outside and ask! I suppose there should've been security outside but there wasn't. AND she didn't even bother giving me a receipt. The breakfast buffet isn't worth the money so unless you have a free voucher (which I had and think I have a leftover one if anyone wants - expires 8.28) don't bother. It's pretty gross if you really think about it, then again, so are most hotel breakfast buffets. It's a fine place to crash, it's worn, and it's luck of the draw on the rooms and people who are helpful and know their stuff. And be careful, the doors sometimes don't close and lock properly without a good, strong pull/push, and make sure the maids close them properly too!	
Aug 23 2003	You get what you pay for	It's seen better days. It's clean. It's full of smoke. They are making improvements. The Center Stage restaurant is actually very good. Good convention/meeting facilities.	
Aug 16 2003	Great trip thanks to the Plaza	Just got back from the Plaza, had a great trip. We drove 20 hours to get there and arrived earlier then expected, there was no problem checking in early and they made sure we were in the same tower as the couples we were meeting there. (they had booked separately). The staff was very friendly and helpful. We were in the south tower on the 23rd floor facing south to the strip, it was a great view at night. The room was big but the bathroom was a little tight, certainly not bad enough to be a problem. Easy access to the FSE which was a great time. The party atmosphere on Fremont street is a lot of fun and you are truely withing easy walking distance from half a dozen other casinos, not like the strip where you may need to day plan just to walk to the next casino. The Poker room was very friendly and they made sure the comped drinks were frequent and fairly strong. All in all we spent about 20 hours in our room in three days which made the $23 a night a great bargin.	
